article.headline: S. Dakota State 50, Stephen F.Austin 48
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Kyle Minett's 1-yard touchdown run with no time left gave South Dakota State a wild 50-48 come-from-behind win over Stephen F. Austin on Saturday night. The Lumberjacks had gone ahead 48-44 on Tyrone Ross' 14-yard scoring reception from Jeremy Moses with 41 seconds remaining. Minett's game-winning run, his third TD of the night, capped a 30-point fourth quarter for the Jackrabbits. South Dakota State (3-2) trailed 24-6 at halftime. Ryan Berry hit 30-of-44 passes for 350 yards and two touchdowns for the Jackrabbits. He threw two interceptions. Glen Fox had nine catches for 103 yards and a score. Minett finished with 103 yards on 33 carries for South Dakota State and caught seven passes for 92 yards. Moses was 34-of-51 for 370 yards with five touchdowns and four interceptions for the Lumberjacks (1-3). Duane Brooks caught nine passes for 107 yards, and Tyrone Ross had two catches for touchdowns.
